OL,3,CReform complains to BBC about
OL,4,CCaerphilly by-election debate 'plant'
OL,6,FDuring the debate, a woman criticised
OL,7,Fthe party's stance on immigration,
OL,8,Fclaiming she had "never felt so
OL,9,Funwelcome in my own home town",
OL,10,Ftelling Reform candidate Llyr Powell:
OL,11,F"Mr Powell, I blame you for that."
OL,13,FThe interaction went viral and was
OL,14,Fdiscussed for the remainder of the
OL,15,Fcampaign, the party said.
OL,17,FPlaid candidate Lindsay Whittle went
OL,18,Fon to win with 15,961 votes, more than
OL,19,F47% of the total.
